The paper discusses self-improving algorithms for sorting and Delaunay triangulation under a group product distribution model. This involves analyzing the behavior of fixed unknown functions of hidden variables, which suggests a focus on data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of entropy and product distributions also suggests information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC) as relevant sub-categories. Finally, the self-improving aspect of the algorithms may involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques.
